name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Timberline High School -6120 Mullen Rd SE, Lacey WA, 98503
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

• This is a walk-in clinic at Timberline High School located at 6120 Mullen Rd SE, Lacey WA, 98503 • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with warm layers. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
